Package com.cafean.client.analysis

Class AbstractComponent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.analysis.GenericObject
      • com.cafean.client.analysis.AbstractComponent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Checkable, ComponentElement, IdentHolder, ModelElement, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractBeanComponent, Connection, UserDefinedFunction, UserDefinedValue, ViewComponent
    public abstract class AbstractComponent
extends GenericObject
implements java.lang.Cloneable, ComponentElement, Checkable
    The base class for ModelEditor Components. This should no longer be directly extended by plug-ins. Extend the AbstractBeanComponent class instead.
    See Also:
    ComponentList, ComponentListener

      • getIntegralComponents

        public AbstractComponent[] getIntegralComponents​(java.util.List included)
        Returns an array of the components that are considered to be an integral part of this component. These integral components should be carried along during copy/paste operations regardless of whether this component is part of the initial selection or not.

        Typically, the components returned by this method are not conceptually separate from this one. They are encapsulated in AbstractComponent implementations for convenience only.

        Parameters:
        included - a List containing the components included in the current copy operation. This list should not be modified.
        Returns:
        an AbstractComponent[] containing references to all this components' integral components. Duplicate references will not be copied multiple times.

      • getNewCompIdent

        public int getNewCompIdent​(int dbid,
                           boolean preserveUnresolved,
                           boolean useDbId)
        Retrieves the ident of the component with the given DB_ID in this component's model. This is used when resolving copy/paste operations, and the original primary key (ident) has been adjusted to be unique in the target model. This method searches through the components in the current model If dbid is 0, a 0 is returned.
        Parameters:
        dbid - the primary key of the target component.
        preserveUnresolved - if true, and no component is found dbid will be returned. if false, 0 will be returned.
        useDbId - if true, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByDB_ID; if false, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByIdent
        Returns:
        the new component primary key.

      • userDelete

        public javax.swing.undo.UndoableEdit userDelete​(java.util.List context)
        Performs all additional operations required in order to properly delete this component from its model. This will not be called for Connection type components as they can be handled in userDisconnect

        This empty base implementation is sufficient for nearly all components and simply returns null.

        In some plug-in specific cases other components may require notification that this component is about to be deleted by the user. In these cases an UndoableEdit for the changes to these components should be returned by this method.

        NOTE: This method does not handle the creation of the UndoableDelete for this component and serves only as a point of entry for additional undoable operations to be performed.

        Parameters:
        context - a List initially containing the components being deleted. Additional objects can be added to this list for use by subsequent components inside their userDelete methods.
        Returns:
        an UndoableEdit capable of undoing the additional required operations. This returned edit will be added to the deletion's CompoundEdit just before the UndoableDelete that includes this component.
        See Also:
        removeVerify(), UndoableDelete

      • reconnectImage

        public void reconnectImage​(java.util.Vector sourceComps,
                           java.util.Vector destComps)
        Reconnects the internal linkage of this component not handled by reconnectIdentReferences and rebuildConnections during a copy and/or paste operation.

        This method is called on the source component and is intended to rebuild appropriate structures for the destination component. (likely found by the destination's DB_ID matching the source's ident)/.

        Parameters:
        sourceComps - a Vector containing the components in the source model being reconnected
        destComps - a Vector containing the components in the destination model being reconnected

      • rebuildConnections

        public void rebuildConnections​(java.util.Vector sourceComps,
                               java.util.Vector destComps)
        Rebuilds this component's related Connection objects using the given component Vectors as a guide.

        For direct references, the source list is used to determine which connections to preserve and the image list to make the new connections. For ident references reconnectIdentReferences is used.

        NOTE: This base implementation is sufficient in all known cases.

        Parameters:
        sourceComps - the Vector that contains the original components of the copy paste operation.
        destComps - the Vector that contains the target components of the copy paste operation.

      • complete

        public boolean complete​(InsertionSource insertSource)
        This method uses an InsertionSource object to completely control the insertion of this component. A valid implementation of this method must handle adding the component to the target model, initializing the component, and adding an appropriate undo-able edit to the source's CompoundEdit.

        When this method is called, this component has not been added to the model available from InsertionSource.getModel(). Refer to the source code documentation for InsertionSource for more information on this process.

        Note: Components that implement this method should not implement complete() as it will not be called if this method returns true.

        Parameters:
        insertSource - the InsertionSource that should be used to guide the component insertion process.
        Returns:
        true if this component supports component initialization via an InsertionSource object; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        InsertionSource.componentAdded(AbstractComponent, boolean), InsertionSource.getEdit(), InsertionSource.getModel()

      • reconnectIdentReferences

        public void reconnectIdentReferences​(boolean preserveUnresolved,
                                     boolean useDbId)
        Description copied from class: GenericObject
        Resets this component's internal ident references to refer to appropriate components in the current AbstractModel. Intended for use after adding a component to a model and thus it's DB_ID will have been set to it's ident in the previous model. For ident references use find__ByDbId to find the new component, then store it's ident.

        Note: If this component's DB_ID is 0 this method does nothing.

        Specified by:
        reconnectIdentReferences in interface IdentHolder
        Overrides:
        reconnectIdentReferences in class GenericObject
        Parameters:
        preserveUnresolved - if true, ident references that aren't resolvable will be left dangling, if false, they will be set to 0.
        useDbId - if true, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByDB_ID; if false, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByIdent
